HEADWORD: Undercliff
<hw>Un"der*cliff`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A subordinate
cliff on a shore, consisting of material that has fallen from the higher
cliff above.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

